The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to predict algorithm runtime, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of various models and techniques for building these predictions, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the application of these predictions to algorithm analysis and software engineering, which could fall under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
